The paper discusses a data-processing framework that provides high-throughput, low-latency incremental view maintenance for a general class of iterative data-parallel computations, including SQL, stratified Datalog with negation and non-monotonic aggregates, and much of graph processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Databases (cs.DB), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
